[11.081966, "o", "  \u001b[2m  Querying NotebookLM Oracle across 40+ sources…\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[11.582247, "o", "  \u001b[0m\u001b[36mFor long-running agents, the Three-Layer Memory Stack is the\u001b[0m\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[11.622587, "o", "  \u001b[0m\u001b[36m  established pattern. Working memory (in-context, fast, volatile)\u001b[0m\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[11.662682, "o", "  \u001b[0m\u001b[36m  handles the current task. Episodic memory (vector store) captures\u001b[0m\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[11.702813, "o", "  \u001b[0m\u001b[36m  what happened across sessions. Semantic memory (knowledge graph\u001b[0m\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[11.74311, "o", "  \u001b[0m\u001b[36m  or wiki) stores what the agent has learned permanently.\u001b[0m\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[11.783405, "o", "  \u001b[0m\u001b[36m\u001b[0m\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[11.823749, "o", "  \u001b[0m\u001b[36m  The Keeper governs all three layers. Its rule: never let working\u001b[0m\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[11.864239, "o", "  \u001b[0m\u001b[36m  memory overflow into the context window. Summarise first.\u001b[0m\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[11.90426, "o", "  \u001b[0m\u001b[36m  Persist second. Retrieve only what's needed.\u001b[0m\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[11.944512, "o", "  \u001b[0m\u001b[36m\u001b[0m\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[11.984804, "o", "  \u001b[0m\u001b[36m  Sources: three-layer-memory-stack.md, langgraph.md, mem0 research\u001b[0m\u001b[0m\r\n"]
